{% macro render_error_monitoring_checklist() -%}
#### Error Monitoring Checklist

```
Error Logging & Monitoring:
- [ ] All exceptions logged with context (not silent swallows)
- [ ] Error logging includes request/operation ID for tracing
- [ ] Sensitive data (passwords, tokens) never logged
- [ ] Errors include timestamp and logger name
- [ ] Structured logging for machine-readable errors
- [ ] Errors are categorized (warn, error, critical)
- [ ] Retryable errors logged at WARN level
- [ ] Non-retryable errors logged at ERROR level
- [ ] System failures logged at CRITICAL level
- [ ] Error messages are actionable (not cryptic)
- [ ] Error rates monitored in metrics/dashboards
- [ ] Alerts configured for error thresholds
- [ ] Error patterns analyzed weekly
- [ ] Stack traces included for debugging
- [ ] User-facing errors are helpful (not technical)
```

